data.event: Before the 1900s, the village of Muara was inhabited by a small group of Malay fishermen.

event.title: The development of the Serai Pimping area for coal extraction in 1883

data.event: The development of the Serai Pimping area for coal extraction in 1883 for steamships, and later settlement of the area as Brooketon by Charles Brooke, the White Rajah of Sarawak in 1889 saw rapid development of the area.
